pull_request.body:
this is the v12 version of https://github.com/OCA/server-tools/tree/9.0/oauth_provider

Note I added a few changes on top of the migration:

- previously, the permissions on clients and some other models were too lax. in v12, only managers have access to clients and scopes, everything else goes via sudo(). That's why a bunch of methods are private now
- implemented client type `backend application`
- implemented http auth method `oauth_provider`

Those involved some necessary refactoring, that's why I rolled that together.

issue.title: [14.0] nl tax statement - Error since upgrade from 13 to 14
issue.body:
<!-- Provide a general summary of the issue in the Title above.
Before opening the issue, please check that there isn't another issue addressing the same problem already created -->

## Module
l10n_nl_vat_statement.py

## Describe the bug
System creates error when running the Dutch btw report functionality
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 410, in statement_update
    self._set_statement_lines(lines, move_lines)
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 437, in _set_statement_lines
    tags_map = self._get_tags_map()
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 388, in _get_tags_map
    matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})

## To Reproduce
Affected version: 14.0 (earlier this problem was already resolved in version 13.0)

Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Difficult to reproduce, since in a vanilla environment this issue does not occur
2.  I had this problem before (after upgrade from 12 -> 13 and at that time it was fixed by making the code change as described below.
3. Problem came up directly after migrating: I simply ran the Dutch btw report and clicked "refresh" to find the relevant vat lines. That led to the error as described above.
4. This happened both in the existing declarations and in a new declaration.

**Expected behavior**
I had expected that the system would have found the corresponding btw line items

**Proposed code change (based on the same problem in version 13.0) - I tested it and it resolves the problem in 14.0.
Module: l10n_nl_vat_statement.py
Start of removal
        for tag in nl_tags:
            res_code = pattern_code.match(tag.name)
            if re.search("omzet", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})
            elif re.search("btw", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "btw")})
            elif res_code:
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), False)})
End of removal

Start of insertion
        for tag in nl_tags:
            res_code = pattern_code.match(tag.name)
            if res_code and re.search("omzet", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})
            elif res_code and re.search("btw", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "btw")})
            elif res_code:
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), False)})
End of insertion

**Additional context**
See [https://github.com/OCA/l10n-netherlands/issues/318] for the same behaviour and corresponding fix in version 13.

comment.body:
The error mentioned in the description of the bug is caused by wrong account tags for taxes, as explained also in 
https://github.com/OCA/l10n-netherlands/issues/318 so that error is a "symptom" that something is wrong.

The proposed code change is just hiding the error but is not fixing the root of the problem which is the wrong data (tags for taxes). We need a proper fix of the issue, that would be the fixing of the data, like Cas was doing, with a dedicated script. But for that we need to analyze what's going wrong in that particular database.

The proposed code change is still valid IMO and I'm thinking of including it when porting the module to V15, however that could cause a more difficult detection of wrong tax tags.

issue.title: [14.0] Incomplete TAX statement due to missing partner fiscal position.
issue.body:
## l10n_nl_tax_statement


## Tax Statement is missing entries from vendors which do not have a fiscal position set.
The module `l10n_nl_tax_statement` seems to take into account the fiscal postion of the partner.
When the fiscal position on the partner level is not set, the entries from the vendor bills are not included in the tax statment.
From an usability point this is undisered as one does not know that the statement is incomplete.

Likely caused because the fiscal position is not automatically populated on the chart of accounts when one sets the vatnumber on the partner.


## To Reproduce
**Affected versions**: 14.0

Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Install dutch chart of accounts
2. Create a partner by entering name and vat number. (is company)
3. Register an vendor bill for that partner
4.  Generate a tax statement

**Expected behavior**
- Complete generation of tax statement. If there are partners with invoices and no fiscal position raise a warning that the tax statement might be incomplete. Show in the error on which partners that is the case.
- Auto populate the fiscal_position from the vat number (or country code of the partner)


**Additional context**
Could be that this should be handled in odoo natively. But posting here as the effect occurs on the oca tax statement module. And a lot of accounting features have moved to community.


Offcourse an user error is the cause of this as the user should have configured the partner correctly. 
Yet, it is an common error as the fiscal position is not mandatory.
The field is only visible when clicking on the sales&purhase tab. Secondly it is troublesome as one is unaware the statement could be incomplete.

comment.body:
@bosd I tried to reproduce the issue you mentioned. I tried both on runbot and locally. In case the fiscal position is not set, I'm always able to get the tax amount under "5b Voorbelasting" (for vendor bills). So to me it seems that the tax statement report works properly, regardless of the fiscal position value.
I also checked the code and I didn't find any possible correlation with the fiscal position.

issue.body:
<!-- Provide a general summary of the issue in the Title above.
Before opening the issue, please check that there isn't another issue addressing the same problem already created -->

## Module
l10n_nl_vat_statement.py

## Describe the bug
System creates error when running the Dutch btw report functionality
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 410, in statement_update
    self._set_statement_lines(lines, move_lines)
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 437, in _set_statement_lines
    tags_map = self._get_tags_map()
  File "/var/lib/odoo/addons/14.0/l10n_nl_tax_statement/models/l10n_nl_vat_statement.py", line 388, in _get_tags_map
    matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})

## To Reproduce
Affected version: 14.0 (earlier this problem was already resolved in version 13.0)

Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Difficult to reproduce, since in a vanilla environment this issue does not occur
2.  I had this problem before (after upgrade from 12 -> 13 and at that time it was fixed by making the code change as described below.
3. Problem came up directly after migrating: I simply ran the Dutch btw report and clicked "refresh" to find the relevant vat lines. That led to the error as described above.
4. This happened both in the existing declarations and in a new declaration.

**Expected behavior**
I had expected that the system would have found the corresponding btw line items

**Proposed code change (based on the same problem in version 13.0) - I tested it and it resolves the problem in 14.0.
Module: l10n_nl_vat_statement.py
Start of removal
        for tag in nl_tags:
            res_code = pattern_code.match(tag.name)
            if re.search("omzet", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})
            elif re.search("btw", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "btw")})
            elif res_code:
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), False)})
End of removal

Start of insertion
        for tag in nl_tags:
            res_code = pattern_code.match(tag.name)
            if res_code and re.search("omzet", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "omzet")})
            elif res_code and re.search("btw", tag.name, re.IGNORECASE):
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), "btw")})
            elif res_code:
                matching.update({tag.id: (res_code.group(0), False)})
End of insertion

**Additional context**
See [https://github.com/OCA/l10n-netherlands/issues/318] for the same behaviour and corresponding fix in version 13.

comment.body:
The error mentioned in the description of the bug is caused by wrong account tags for taxes, as explained also in 
https://github.com/OCA/l10n-netherlands/issues/318 so that error is a "symptom" that something is wrong.

The proposed code change is just hiding the error but is not fixing the root of the problem which is the wrong data (tags for taxes). We need a proper fix of the issue, that would be the fixing of the data, like Cas was doing, with a dedicated script. But for that we need to analyze what's going wrong in that particular database.

The proposed code change is still valid IMO and I'm thinking of including it when porting the module to V15, however that could cause a more difficult detection of wrong tax tags.

issue.title: [14.0] Incomplete TAX statement due to missing partner fiscal position.
issue.body:
## l10n_nl_tax_statement


## Tax Statement is missing entries from vendors which do not have a fiscal position set.
The module `l10n_nl_tax_statement` seems to take into account the fiscal postion of the partner.
When the fiscal position on the partner level is not set, the entries from the vendor bills are not included in the tax statment.
From an usability point this is undisered as one does not know that the statement is incomplete.

Likely caused because the fiscal position is not automatically populated on the chart of accounts when one sets the vatnumber on the partner.


## To Reproduce
**Affected versions**: 14.0

Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Install dutch chart of accounts
2. Create a partner by entering name and vat number. (is company)
3. Register an vendor bill for that partner
4.  Generate a tax statement

**Expected behavior**
- Complete generation of tax statement. If there are partners with invoices and no fiscal position raise a warning that the tax statement might be incomplete. Show in the error on which partners that is the case.
- Auto populate the fiscal_position from the vat number (or country code of the partner)


**Additional context**
Could be that this should be handled in odoo natively. But posting here as the effect occurs on the oca tax statement module. And a lot of accounting features have moved to community.


Offcourse an user error is the cause of this as the user should have configured the partner correctly. 
Yet, it is an common error as the fiscal position is not mandatory.
The field is only visible when clicking on the sales&purhase tab. Secondly it is troublesome as one is unaware the statement could be incomplete.

comment.body:
@bosd I tried to reproduce the issue you mentioned. I tried both on runbot and locally. In case the fiscal position is not set, I'm always able to get the tax amount under "5b Voorbelasting" (for vendor bills). So to me it seems that the tax statement report works properly, regardless of the fiscal position value.
I also checked the code and I didn't find any possible correlation with the fiscal position.

this is the v12 version of https://github.com/OCA/server-tools/tree/9.0/oauth_provider
